gomodel:SYNGO_4644  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1,S1. Structured illumination microscopy (SIM) and immunogold EM show Bin1 localization to the postsynaptic compartment\n\nFigure 4e,f. SIM microscopy shows Bin1 and GluA1 closely co-localize within dendritic spines.. Experimental description: \"Immuno-electron microscopy (immuno-EM)\n\nThe basic approach is as described in [34]. Deeply-anesthetized adult C57/BL6 mice were perfused with mixed aldehyde fixative; brains were removed, post-fixed overnight in the same fixative, and stored in pH 7.2 phosphate buffer.\"\n\nAntibodies;\nBin1 mAb (Millipore Cat# 05-449)\nGluA1 N-term mAb (Millipore Cat# MAB2263)\nGluA1 C-term pAb (Millipore Cat# ABN241)\nSynapsin mAb (CellSignaling Cat# 5297)\nPSD95 mAb (Neuromab Cat# 75-028)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4644" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

